      "decision": "No junction-tree-specific cache diagnostics. Existing per-market cache counters and engine-stats are sufficient. compile_type already exposed in engine-stats response.",
      "based_on": ["q6"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "Separate junction_tree_cache_hits vs current_model_cache_hits — premature, one entry per market means no meaningful distinction"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    }
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "step": 1,
      "task": "Implement JunctionTreeCompiler.compile_result() method in backend/inference/junction_tree.py. Build a minimal BayesianNetworkGraph from the market_snapshot (single variable with its outcomes, zero edges, empty CPTs) and delegate to self.compile_network(). Signature: compile_result(self, *, market_snapshot, conditional_marginals, compile_time_ms, last_updated) -> CompileResult. This makes JunctionTreeCompiler a drop-in replacement for CurrentModelCompiler in the server flow.",
      "depends_on": [],
      "estimated_lines": 25,
      "risk": "medium"
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "task": "Add compiler selection in server.py compile_market_for_inference(). Import JUNCTION_TREE_COMPILER. Select compiler based on ENGINE_CONFIG.compile_type: if 'junction_tree' use JUNCTION_TREE_COMPILER, else CURRENT_MODEL_COMPILER. Replace the hardcoded CURRENT_MODEL_COMPILER.compile_result() call at line 1168 with the selected compiler.",
      "depends_on": [1],
      "estimated_lines": 12,
      "risk": "medium"
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "task": "Add junction tree cache invalidation tests in tests/test_bayes_market_cache_invalidation.py. New test class JunctionTreeCacheTests with tests: (a) compile with junction_tree compiler populates cache, (b) second call returns cached result, (c) probability edit invalidates and produces new compile_id/source_state_hash, (d) cache isolation between markets still holds, (e) junction tree CompileResult has compile_type='junction_tree'. Follow existing test patterns (setUp calls reset_state, use build_probability_edit helper).",
      "depends_on": [1, 2],
      "estimated_lines": 80,
      "risk": "low"
    },
    {
      "step": 4,
      "task": "Run existing test suite to verify no regressions. The existing CacheIntegrationTests use CURRENT_MODEL_COMPILER implicitly — after adding compiler selection, these tests may use junction_tree compiler depending on ENGINE_CONFIG. If so, either: (a) pin those tests to current_model via a test fixture, or (b) verify they pass with junction_tree compiler (preferred since config already says junction_tree). Fix any failures.",
      "depends_on": [2, 3],
      "estimated_lines": 15,
      "risk": "low"
    }
  ],
